This paper deals with differential privacy, which is a topic in cryptography and security (cs.CR). The concept of histograms is commonly used in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the trade-off between privacy and utility, which is a topic in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG). The algorithm proposed in the paper involves information theory and coding techniques (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses applications in social networks and discrete distributions, which fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
